This paper deals with cut-elimination in the modal mu-calculus, which is a logical system used in computer science and mathematics. The paper focuses on the one-variable fragment of the calculus, which suggests that it may fall under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the use of the W-rule in the cut-elimination technique may indicate that the paper could also be classified under Proof Theory (cs.PL) or Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Logic and Verification (cs.LM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) due to the nature of the calculus and its applications in these areas.
